feat(m1-auth-ws-presence): token-bootstrapped auth, WS gateway & live presence

Suggested PR body:
Delivers the M1 acceptance loop (SPEC.md §14): the admin mints an invite token via a server CLI
command; a new user registers in the Tauri client (server URL + token + username + password), logs
in, and the client connects to the WebSocket gateway and renders the member list updating
online/offline live. The session token persists in the OS keychain so a relaunch stays logged in,
and the admin can revoke a user to kill their sessions.

